The evidence with the title 'How much will sea levels rise in the 21st Century? ' says Sea levels are rising due to thermal expansion and melting of land-based ice. Global warming is causing the oceans to absorb alot of extra heat ( up to 90 % ). ... Sea level rise because the rapid melting of the ice sheets and glaciers was not incorporated in the last IPCC  ... Future sea level rises depend on a number of factors . 
